From 4db400e34f770d143d32ecc0de21d9454bf1f225 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@polyedge.dev>
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 2026 12:39:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: strategy tagging for A/B comparison of pipeline
 configurations

Trades now carry a strategy_tag so profiled and unprofiled runs can be
compared side-by-side from the same paper_trades.json file.

core/paper_trader.py:
- PaperTrade gains strategy_tag field (default '' for backward compat)
- enter_trade() accepts strategy_tag parameter
- New compare_strategies() method: per-tag Brier scores, PnL, win rates,
  market overlap analysis, directional disagreement detection

strategies/enriched_edge_detector.py:
- Auto-generates strategy_tag from config: 'enriched', 'enriched+live',
  'enriched+profiles', 'enriched+live+profiles'
- Passes tag through to enter_trade

run_pipeline.py:
- New --report-compare mode for A/B comparison

Usage:
  python run_pipeline.py --enriched                    # tags as 'enriched'
  python run_pipeline.py --enriched --whale-profiles   # tags as 'enriched+profiles'
  python run_pipeline.py --report-compare              # side-by-side comparison

Backward compatible: old trades without strategy_tag load as 'untagged'.
---
 core/paper_trader.py                 | 128 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 run_pipeline.py                      |   4 +
 strategies/enriched_edge_detector.py |  10 ++-
 3 files changed, 140 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

